# Sibyl Design Principles

This rule ensures all frontend work follows the design system. See [design-system.md](mdc:docs/design-system.md) for the full specification.

## Quick Reference

### Color Palette (Warm Cream)
- **Background**: `#fff6e9` — never pure white `#ffffff` except PDF pages
- **Text**: warm browns only — `#4a3c2e` body, `#6b5344` labels, `#8b7355` muted
- **Muted surfaces**: `#eddfc8` — never cold `slate-50/100` greys
- **Borders**: `#e0d4bf` — never `slate-200`

### Prohibited
- ❌ `text-slate-400`, `text-slate-500`, `text-slate-600` — use warm browns
- ❌ `bg-slate-50`, `bg-slate-100` — use `bg-[#f5ecdb]`, `bg-[#eddfc8]`
- ❌ `border border-slate-200` on containers — use spacing/negative space
- ❌ `rounded-xl` on content cards — flat edges, no rounding
- ❌ Bubble backgrounds on AI chat responses — plain text only
- ❌ Emojis anywhere — use Lucide React icons

### Container Styling
```tsx
// ✅ Correct — no border, no rounding
<div className="bg-[#fff6e9] p-5">

// ❌ Wrong — has border and rounding
<div className="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-5">
```

### Text Colors
```tsx
// ✅ Correct warm browns
<span className="text-[#4a3c2e]">Body text</span>
<span className="text-[#6b5344]">Label text</span>
<span className="text-[#8b7355]">Muted hint</span>

// ❌ Wrong cold greys
<span className="text-slate-600">Body text</span>
<span className="text-slate-500">Label text</span>
<span className="text-slate-400">Muted hint</span>
```

### Semantic Colors (allowed)
- Verified: `emerald-500` / `#10b981`
- Contradicted: `rose-500` / `#f43f5e`
- Unverified: `amber-500` / `#f59e0b`

### Icons
Always use **Lucide React**. Never use emojis or inline SVGs.
